<headline>Special Weather Statement issued December 28 at 8:37PM EST  by NWS Detroit</headline>
<description>...Locally Heavy Snow...
A band of intense snowfall rates has developed along and just
south of the I-69 corridor from Lansing to Port Huron. Snowfall
rates will peak around an inch per hour in this band through
roughly 10 PM before this region of snow weakens and transitions
to some freezing drizzle. Given the recent intensification of this
area of snow, some locations may pick up total snowfall amounts
that reach or exceed three inches by late evening. Drivers along
the I-69 corridor should expect snow covered and slick roads and
poor visibilities.</description>
